{% set description %}
  Adjust the placement of the content by using the <bolt-code-snippet display="inline">placement</bolt-code-snippet> prop. It can be set to a specific placement or automatically calculated. It is recommended to use the <bolt-code-snippet display="inline">boundary</bolt-code-snippet> prop in tandem with auto placement. This ensures that the auto placement will happen within a specific container instead of the entire page. The <bolt-code-snippet display="inline">boundary</bolt-code-snippet> prop accepts all selector names (eg: .class, #id, and [attribute]).
{% endset %}

